, and writer.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nbcconnecticut.com/the-scene/archive/West-Hartford-Guy-Makes-Parks-and-Rec-Funny-.html|title=West Hartford Guy Behind Poehler's \"Parks & Recreation\"|work=NBC Connecticut|access-date=2018-10-10|language=en}}</ref>\n*[[Roger Sperry]], neuropsychologist and [[Nobel Prize]] laureate<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/1981/sperry-bio.html |title=Roger W. Sperry - Biographical |website=Nobelprize.org |access-date=March 12, 2016}}</ref>\n*[[David H. Steinberg]], film and television writer and producer.\n*[[Patrick Zimmerli]], composer<ref name=\"we-ha\" />\n*[[Dave Chameides]], Emmy Award winning Director and Cameraman<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0150505/|title=David Chameides|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-01-27}}</ref>\n*Rob \"the Drummer\" Gottfried, motivational speaker and drummer <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://robthedrummer.com/|title=Youth Motivational Speaker {{!}} Anti Substance Abuse {{!}} Anti Bullying {{!}} Rob the Drummer|website=robthedrummer.com|access-date=2020-01-27}}</ref>\n*\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://hall.whps.org/}}\n*[http://www.whps.org/ West Hartford Public Schools Official Site]\n\n{{Central Connecticut Conference |state=expanded}}\n{{West Hartford Public Schools}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in West Hartford, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Schools in Hartford County, Connecticut]]\n[[Category:Public high schools in Connecticut]]\n[[Category:1924 establishments in Connecticut]]\n", "name_user": "64.121.64.88", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eDemographics)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hall_High_School_(Connecticut)"}
{"title_page": "Isabel Valley", "text_new": "'''Isabel Valley''' is a [[valley]] in the [[Diablo Range]] in [[Santa Clara County, California]]. It is also known as '''Santa Isabel Valley'''.\n\nThe mouth of Isabel Valley lies at an elevation of 2,270 feet / 692 meters.  Its head is at {{coord|37|19|17|N|121|29|44|W|display=inline}} at an elevation of 2,480 feet / 756 meters.<ref>{{GNIS|254823|Isabel Valley}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nIsabel Valley was used by the [[Five Joaquins Gang]] of [[Joaquin Murrieta]] to hold stolen horses until they could be driven southward on the [[La Vereda del Monte]].<ref name=Latta>[[Frank Forrest Latta|Frank F. Latta]], JOAQUIN MURRIETA AND HIS HORSE GANGS, Bear State Books, Santa Cruz, California. 1980.</ref>{{rp|431,433}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://www.google.com/maps/place/Isabel+Valley/ Map of Isabel Valley]\n\n{{coord|37|19|23|N|121|33|23|W|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Valleys of Santa Clara County, California]]\n[[Category:La Vereda del Monte]]\n", "text_old": "'''Isabel Valley''' is a [[valley]] in the [[Diablo Range]] in [[Santa Clara County, California]]. It is also known as '''Santa Isabel Valley'''.\n\nThe mouth of Isabel Valley lies at an elevation of 2,270 feet / 692 meters.  Its head is at {{coord|37|19|17|N|121|29|44|W|display=inline}} at an elevation of 2,480 feet / 756 meters.<ref>{{GNIS|254823|Isabel Valley}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nIsabel Valley was used by the [[Five Joaquins Gang]] of [[Joaquin Murrieta]] to hold stolen horses until they could be driven southward on the [[La Vereda del Monte]].<ref name=Latta>[[Frank Forrest Latta|Frank F. Latta]], JOAQUIN MURRIETA AND HIS HORSE GANGS, Bear State Books, Santa Cruz, California. 1980.</ref>{{rp|431,433}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{coord|37|19|23|N|121|33|23|W|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Valleys of Santa Clara County, California]]\n[[Category:La Vereda del Monte]]\n", "name_user": "Wahn", "label": "safe", "comment": "