ia]], U.S.\n| occupation      = {{flatlist|\n* Actress\n* singer\n}}\n| years_active    = 2003\u2013present\n| relatives       = [[Vanessa Marano]] (sister)\n| module          = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| instrument      = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* piano\n}}\n| label           = [[Big Machine Records]] (2015-2016)<br/>[[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]] (2017)<br/>Flip Phone Records (2018-present)\n| website         = {{URL|lauramarano.com}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Laura Marie Marano'''<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=fOrPBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA6&lpg=PA6&dq=laura+marie+marano#v=onepage&q=laura%20marie%20marano&f=false|title=Laura Marano: Famous Actress & Singer: Famous Actress and Singer|last=Tieck|first=Sarah|date=January 1, 2015|publisher=ABDO|isbn=9781629693330|language=en}}</ref> (born November 29, 1995)<ref name=medianet/> is an American actress and singer.  She starred in the [[Disney Channel]] series ''[[Austin & Ally]]''<ref>{{cite news |author=Erin Hill |date=November 19, 2013 |work=Parade |url=http://www.parade.com/231707/erinhill/my-favorite-things-with-austin-allys-laura-marano-childhood-books-xmas-gifts-and-onset-pranks |title='My Favorite Things' ''with Austin & Ally''{{'}}s Laura Marano |accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hollywood.com/news/celebrities/55041005/austin-and-ally-laura-marano |title=Exclusive: Disney's Laura Marano Shares Secrets!|website=Hollywood.com}}</ref> as [[Austin & Ally#Main cast|Ally Dawson]]. Marano was one of the five original classmates in ''[[Are You Smarter than a 5th Grader? (American game show)|Are You Smarter than a 5th Grader?]]''. She starred in ''[[Without a Trace]]'' for three seasons and also ''[[Back to You (TV series)|Back to You]]'', in both instances playing the daughter of the main characters. Marano starred in the indie film ''[[A Sort of Homecoming (film)|A Sort of Homecoming]]''.<ref>{{cite news |author=Dave McNary |date=January 28, 2014 |url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/laura-marano-starring-in-a-sort-of-homecoming-exclusive-1201075284/ |title=Laura Marano Starring in 'A Sort of Homecoming' (Exclusive) |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=February 2, 2014}}</ref> Marano also starred in the 2015 [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Bad Hair Day (film)|Bad Hair Day]]''.<ref name=BadHairVariety>{{cite news|author=<!-- Variety staff report -->|url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/bad-hair-day-laura-marano-leigh-allyn-baker-disney-channel-original-movie-1201259014/ |title='Bad Hair Day': Laura Marano, Leigh-Allyn Baker to Star in Disney Channel Original Movie |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=July 8, 2014 |accessdate=July 27, 2014}}</ref> In 2019 Marano starred in the [[Netflix]] original movie ''[[The Perfect Date]]''.\n\nIn 2015, she signed with [[Big Machine Records]] and released her debut single \"[[Boombox (song)|Boombox]]\" on March 11, 2016 and \"La La\" later that year. On October 5, 2018, Laura Marano released the single \"Me\" as an independent artist.\n\n==Early life==\nMarano was born in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]. She is the daughter of college professor Damiano Marano and former actress Ellen Marano, who owns the Agoura Children's Theatre.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.vcstar.com/news/2009/jan/25/agoura-hills-sisters-are-young-stars-on-the-rise/ | title=Agoura Hills sisters are young stars on the rise | author=Jeffrey Dransfeldt | date=January 25, 2009 | work=Ventura County Star | accessdate=February 7, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://agourachildrenstheatre.com/About_Us.html | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011060136/http://agourachildrenstheatre.com/About_Us.html | url-status=dead | archive-date=October 11, 2008 | title=About Us | publisher=Agoura Children's Theatre }}</ref> Her father is of Italian descent.<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://tommy2.net/content/?p=45042 |title=Interview: Laura Marano |website=Tommy2.net |accessdate=December 20, 2013}}</ref> Marano was first introduced to acting at her mother's theatre. At age 5, Marano began expressing interest in acting professionally to her parents along with her older sister [[Vanessa Marano|Vanessa]], who is also an actress. However, her mother had trepidation about the idea of her daughters working in the tough industry of acting. She took them to one of the strictest talent agents in Abrams Talent Agency in hopes that they would be rejected and then lose interest. To her surprise, the agency wanted both Laura and Vanessa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vcstar.com/entertainment/agoura-hills-sisters-are-young-stars-on-the-rise-ep-372456892-352303971.html|title=Agoura Hills sisters are young stars on the rise|website=vcstar.com}}</ref> From there, Marano began her career.\n\nMarano attended traditional school while she worked, even when she booked a full-time job on ''Austin & Ally'', instead of doing school on set. \"I go to an actual high school and my friends and everybody there have been so supportive,\" said Marano. \"It's nice when I'm not working to go to that school and be surrounded by really supportive friends.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2013/04/09/laura-marano-goes-to-a-regular-high-school/ |title=Laura Marano Goes To A Regular High School |publisher=Disney Dreaming |date=April 9, 2013 |accessdate=December 20, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===2003\u20132010: ''Without a Trace'' and ''Back to You''===\nMarano's first acting role was when she was five years old.<ref>{{cite web| date=July 23, 2012 | title=Vanessa & Laura Marano Interview - 2012 Teen Choice Awards | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ppuj5ZD_loA | via=[[YouTube]] | publisher=clevverTV | accessdate=February 7, 2013}}</ref> Since then, she worked for multiple productions at the Stage Door Theater. She has appeared in numerous commercials and had small roles on ''[[Ghost Whisperer]]'', ''[[Medical Investigation]]'', ''[[Huff (TV series)|Huff]]'' and ''[[Joan of Arcadia]]''. Her bigger roles in television have been in ''[[Without a Trace]]'' and other shows. She played the child role of [[Keira Knightley]]'s character in the film ''[[The Jacket]]'' and had a small flashback role in the film ''[[Superbad (film)|Superbad]]''. She was a regular cast member on the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] [[game show]], ''[[Are You Smarter than a 5th Grader?]]'' and played the role of Gracie Carr on FOX's sitcom ''[[Back to You (TV series)|Back to You]]''. Marano has since appeared in several episodes of ''[[The Sarah Silverman Program]]''. Initially she was cast in the pilot episode, \"[[List of The Sarah Silverman Program episodes|Batteries]]\", as the child version of [[Sarah Silverman]], and the writers liked her so much they brought her back for a larger role as a girl Sarah coaches to win a beauty pageant (\"[[List of The Sarah Silverman Program episodes|Not Without My Daughter]]\"). On the DVD commentary track, co-star [[Brian Posehn]] notes that Marano knew everyone else's lines better than they did. She also appeared in ''[[Dexter (TV series)|Dexter]]'' as the child version of [[List of Dexter characters#Debra Morgan|Debra Morgan]]. She also played the child version of a character played by [[Diana Scarwid]], Alice Shaw, sister of [[Angela Petrelli]], on ''[[Heroes (American TV series)|Heroes]]''.\n\n===2011\u20132016: ''Austin & Ally'' and radio===\nIn 2011, Marano starred as Ally Dawson on the [[Disney Channel]] series ''[[Austin & Ally]]''.<ref name=aa_110111/><ref name=\"HRrenew2\"/> In 2013, Marano recorded four solo songs and one duet with [[Ross Lynch]] for the [[soundtrack album]] ''[[Austin & Ally: Turn It Up]]''.<ref name=TurnItUp>{{cite web|title=Austin & Ally: Turn It Up (Soundtrack from the TV Series)|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/redial/id738604085?i=738604094|publisher=Itunes|accessdate=October 2, 2014}}</ref> \"Me and You\" debuted within the U.S. [[Billboard charts|''Billboard'' Kid Digital Songs]] chart at number thirteen before rising to the sixth spot, spending eleven weeks on the chart.<ref name=KidDigitalSongs>{{cite web|title=Artists / Laura Marano - Billboard Chart History|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/5882326/laura-marano/chart?sort=date&f=1103|work=Billboard|accessdate=October 2, 2014}}</ref> \"Redial\" debuted at number nineteen before peaking at number eighteen, spending four weeks on the chart.<ref name=KidDigitalSongs /> Also in 2013, Marano recorded a duet with her ''Austin & Ally'' co-star Ross Lynch entitled \"I Love Christmas\" for [[Disney Channel]]'s third holiday compilation album, ''[[Disney Holidays Unwrapped|Holidays Unwrapped]]''.<ref name=ILoveChristmas>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/i-love-christmas-single/id739393028|title=I Love Christmas - Single by Ross Lynch & Laura Marano|publisher=Zobbel|accessdate=October 17, 2012}}</ref> On November 25, 2013, the song was released as a promotional single.<ref name=ILoveChristmas/> On December 14, \"I Love Christmas\" debuted within the U.S. [[Billboard charts|''Billboard'' Holiday Digital Songs]] chart peaking at number fifty.<ref name=HolidayChart>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2013-12-14/holiday-season-digital-songs|title=December 14, 2013 - Holiday Digital Songs|work=Billboard |date=September 8, 2012 |accessdate=September 13, 2012}}</ref> Marano sings, dances, and writes songs. She hopes to perform in stage musicals in the future.<ref>{{cite news |author=Malcolm Lewis Barnes |date=November 27, 2013 |work=[[The Washington Times]] |url=http://www.freenewspos.com/news/article/e/224240/today/teen-star-laura-marano-surprises-students-at-leckie-elementary-school |title=Teen Star Laura Marano Surprises Students at Leckie Elementary |accessdate=May 18, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924015625/http://www.freenewspos.com/news/article/e/224240/today/teen-star-laura-marano-surprises-students-at-leckie-elementary-school |archivedate=September 24, 2015  }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IZ7e9cpPAXo |title=Hanging With Austin & Ally - Part 5 Laura Marano Interview - Disney Channel Official |via=YouTube |date=April 3, 2013 |accessdate=December 20, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Marano voiced as Rachel in four episodes of ''[[Randy Cunningham: 9th Grade Ninja]]''. She also appeared as Hammu in ''[[Fish Hooks]]'' and as Fangs in ''[[Liv and Maddie]]''. Also in 2014, she appeared in a music video produced for British pop-rock group [[The Vamps (British band)|The Vamps]] and American singer [[Demi Lovato]] called \"[[Somebody to You]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pressparty.com/pg/newsdesk/TheVamps/view/112079/|title=The Vamps on casting Laura Marano in their 'Somebody To You' music video: Pressparty|work=Pressparty|accessdate=January 11, 2015}}</ref> In March 2015, Marano stated that she had signed a record deal with Universal's [[Big Machine Records]].<ref name=THRMachine>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/kids-choice-awards-2015-iggy-785161|title=Kids' Choice Awards 2015: Iggy Azalea Begged Producers to Get Slimed|author=Liz Isenberg|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=March 30, 2015}}</ref> In the same year, Marano starred in Disney Channel's Original Movie, ''[[Bad Hair Day (film)|Bad Hair Day]]''. The film was first released on February 6, 2015 on [[Disney Channel]] and had its premiere broadcast in the US on February 13.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7h2GnpGi2rM | title=Bad Hair Day (Trailer) | via=YouTube | date=February 19, 2015 | accessdate=February 22, 2015 | publisher=Family Channel}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.foxtel.com.au/content/dam/foxtel/whats-on/pdfs/a-z-movies/A-Z_MovieGuide_April15.pdf | title=April 2015 &ndash; A-Z Movies | work=[[Foxtel]] | location=Australia | accessdate=May 12, 2015 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304112407/https://www.foxtel.com.au/content/dam/foxtel/whats-on/pdfs/a-z-movies/A-Z_MovieGuide_April15.pdf | archivedate=March 4, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> She also starring as the young version of Amy in ''[[A Sort of Homecoming (film)|A Sort of Homecoming]]'', which tells the story of a girl who returns to her home town in Louisiana from her career in [[New York City]] upon request of her high school debate coach. In flashbacks, she recalls her senior year, the politics surrounding debate competitions.<ref name=\"robly.com\">{{cite web |title=2015 Announcing Best Actor and Actress Nominations for WorldFest-Houston 48th |url=https://www.robly.com/archive?id=e1e2acb9be28ca46fec6a072abc9b34b |website=robly.com}}</ref> On January 10, 2016, ''Austin and Ally'' ended after four seasons.<ref name=FinaleEp>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/austin-and-ally-series-finale-disney-channel-ross-lynch-laura-marano-1201673922/|title=Disney's ''Austin & Ally'' Creators Talk Series Finale, Favorite Cast Memories|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|author=Elizabeth Wagmeister|date=January 8, 2016|accessdate=January 10, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn January 13, 2016, Marano debuted her own radio talk show on [[Radio Disney]] entitled ''For the Record with Laura Marano''. The weekly one-hour show chronicles Marano's journey as she launches her music career, featuring interviews with a guest star in each episode. The show also provides listeners tips on how one can pursue a career in music.<ref>[http://www.bigmachinelabelgroup.com/big-machine-records-recording-artist-laura-marano-to-host-weekly-show-on-radio-disney/ ]{{dead link|date=April 2020}}</ref> The show has featured various guest stars including [[Nick Jonas]], [[Ariana Grande]], [[Meghan Trainor]], [[OneRepublic]], and [[Troye Sivan]]. The first episode of the show, which aired January 12, 2016, guest starred her co-stars of ''Austin & Ally''.\n\n===2016\u2013present: Films and music===\nOn March 11, 2016, Marano released her debut single called \"[[Boombox (Laura Marano song)|Boombox]]\". The music video for the single released on April 4, 2016 and accumulated over 6 million views in a week. The video currently holds over 50 million views. It guest stars actor and comedian [[Ken Jeong]], along with his daughter Zooey, and was directed by [[Cole Walliser]]. On April 30, 2016, Marano performed the single at the [[2016 Radio Disney Music Awards]], which aired on Disney Channel on May 1. Marano also performed the song on ''[[Today (American TV program)|Today]]'' as [[Elvis Duran]]'s [[Elvis Duran's Artist of the Month|Artist of the Month]] on May 31, 2016. Marano released her second single, \"La La\", on August 25, 2016.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Laura Marano |user=lauramarano |number=764294032595968001 |date=August 12, 2016 |title=Laura Marano La La 8.25.16 |access-date=}}</ref> At the end of 2016, [[Big Machine Records]] made the decision to drop all of their pop artists, except for [[Taylor Swift]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7654398/american-idol-nick-fradiani-big-machine-records-split |title='American Idol' Winner Nick Fradiani, Big Machine Records Part Ways |website=Billboard.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref> On May 18, 2017, it was announced that Marano had signed to [[Warner Bros. Records]] in 2017.<ref name=\"billboard.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/7800858/laura-marano-warner-bros-records-deal|title=Laura Marano Signs to Warner Bros Records|website=Billboard}}</ref> In 2018, they parted ways, because the people who had signed her left [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[YouTube]]|title=Laura Marano Q&A {{!}} Where have I been? New Music? Life Update!|date=October 1, 2018|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z-zm4Fkn0E8|access-date=October 5, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn October 1, 2018, Marano announced in a Q&A video posted on her YouTube channel that she would be releasing new music as an independent artist. She named her own label Flip Phone Records, as Marano is known for not owning a smartphone and still using a flip phone.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://people.com/celebrity/laura-marano-reveals-why-she-still-uses-a-flip-phone/|title='Boombox' Singer Laura Marano Reveals Why She Still Uses a Flip Phone|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=October 5, 2018|language=en}}</ref> On October 5, 2018, she released the single \"Me\" .<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/lauramarano/status/1046928995671916544|title=Me. Out October 5th pic.twitter.com/mFZJH0T4Eg|first=Laura|last=Marano|website=Twitter.com|date=October 1, 2018}}</ref> In January 2019, she released the single \"Let Me Cry\" along with its music video. In February 2019, Marano performed at the [[Roxy Theatre (West Hollywood)|Roxy Theatre]] in Los Angeles and released the single \"F.E.O.U.\". On March 8, 2019, she released her debut [[Extended play|EP]], ''Me'', featuring two unheard tracks and a new remix to \"F.E.O.U.\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/lauramarano/status/1104069336719716352|title=My little baby is officially out I. Am. So. Excited!!!!! |first=Laura|last=Marano|website=Twitter.com|date=March 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\nIn August 2013, Marano was named the 2013 [[UNICEF]]'s [[Trick-or-Treat for UNICEF]] Ambassador, which encouraged children to raise money on Halloween to help children around the world. About the campaign, Laura said \"I'm so excited to celebrate Halloween this year by encouraging kids to support UNICEF's lifesaving work. The Trick-or-Treat for UNICEF campaign is a fun, easy way for kids to learn about world issues and to help other kids who are less fortunate.\"<ref name=\"UNICEF\">{{cite web|url=http://www.trickortreatforunicef.org/disney-channel-star-laura-marano-named-2013-trick-or-treat-unicef-ambassador |title=Disney Channel Star Laura Marano Named 2013 Trick-or-Treat for UNICEF Ambassador |website=Looktothestars.org |date=August 19, 2013 |accessdate=August 26, 2013}}</ref> In August 2014, Marano was ambassador for the Disney and Birds Eye Vegetables campaign 'Step up to the plate'.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wtsp.com/story/entertainment/television/studio10/2014/08/27/teen-actress-joins-chef-in-encouraging-kids-to-eat-healthier/14680845/|title=Laura Marano, from Disney's Austin and Ally, Steps Up to the Plate!|work=[[WTSP]] 10 News|date=August 27, 2014|accessdate=January 11, 2015}}</ref> The campaign's goal is to encourage children in the United States to explore healthy foods such as vegetables.\n\n==Filmography==\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[Finding Nemo]]''\n| Additional voices\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneyabcpress.com/disneychannel/shows/austin-ally/bios/|title=''Austin & Ally'' Show Bios|work=Disney Channel Press|accessdate=January 10, 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160220235118/http://www.disneyabcpress.com/disneychannel/shows/austin-ally/bios/|archivedate=February 20, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.m-magazine.com/posts/13-more-stars-you-had-no-idea-voiced-these-animated-characters-38021/photos/vanessa-laura-marano-38463|title=13 More Stars You Had No Idea Voiced These Animated Characters!|work=[[M Magazine]]|author=Stephanie Osmanski|date=May 7, 2014|accessdate=January 10, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''{{sortname|The|Jacket}}''\n| Young Jackie\n| \n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Ice Age: The Meltdown]]''\n| Additional voices\n| \n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Superbad (film)|Superbad]]''\n| Young Becca\n| \n|-\n| 2015\n| ''{{sortname|A|Sort of Homecoming|dab=film}}''\n| Young Amy\n|\n|-\n|2015\n| ''[[Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip]]''\n| Hotel Babysitter\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Lady Bird (film)|Lady Bird]]''\n| Diana Greenway\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The Perfect Date (film)|The Perf